-- Lubrizol Outlook Is `Sideways,' Hambrick Tells Fox
-- B y   D a n   K r a u t
-- 2012-10-05T21:16:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/lubrizol-outlook-is-sideways-hambrick-tells-fox.html
Lubrizol Chief Executive Officer
James Hambrick, who sold the chemical-additives maker to  Warren Buffett ’s  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  last year, told Fox Business
News that business is pressured by declines in Europe.  “Europe is down a bit, America is kind of going sideways
and Asia is down,” Hambrick told the station in an  interview .
“We’re going sideways. I think we’ll continue to go sideways
through the remainder of this year and on into next year.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dan Kraut in New York at 
